to pay for your drink.

571
00:36:59,750 --> 00:37:01,400
I'm just stopping by.

572
00:37:01,430 --> 00:37:03,070
I'll leave soon.

573
00:37:03,100 --> 00:37:04,100
Mm.

574
00:37:04,460 --> 00:37:05,460
Yu,

575
00:37:05,790 --> 00:37:07,160
thank you so much.

576
00:37:08,020 --> 00:37:09,500
For what?

577
00:37:09,700 --> 00:37:11,750
Thank you for always tutoring me,

578
00:37:12,010 --> 00:37:14,590
and not even charging me anything.

579
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:17,500
You even had to buy me snacks and drinks.

580
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:21,110
You're like a little brother to me.

581
00:37:22,470 --> 00:37:23,470
Yes, Yu.

582
00:37:25,060 --> 00:37:25,870
So, don't worry.

583
00:37:25,910 --> 00:37:26,910
Okay.

584
00:37:41,630 --> 00:37:42,630
Jeab!

585
00:37:50,850 --> 00:37:51,850
Jeab!

586
00:37:53,720 --> 00:37:54,910
Wait for me!

587
00:37:55,420 --> 00:37:56,420
Jeab!

588
00:37:57,810 --> 00:37:58,810
Don't go!

589
00:37:59,610 --> 00:38:00,610
Little Chicken!

590
00:38:07,670 --> 00:38:08,670
Jeab!

591
00:38:16,340 --> 00:38:17,340
Jeab!

592
00:38:19,620 --> 00:38:21,790
I thought I'd never get to
say goodbye to you.

593
00:38:24,110 --> 00:38:25,730
Why are you suddenly changing schools

594
00:38:26,250 --> 00:38:27,290
without telling me?

595
00:38:27,830 --> 00:38:29,690
Where are you going? Is it far?

596
00:38:29,900 --> 00:38:31,920
Why don't you ever
mind your own business?

597
00:38:33,120 --> 00:38:34,120
I...

598
00:38:34,540 --> 00:38:35,700
I... um...

599
00:38:36,410 --> 00:38:38,340
Cat got your tongue? Spit it out.

600
00:38:38,370 --> 00:38:39,980
I just don't want you to change schools.

601
00:38:42,410 --> 00:38:43,820
Is it because

602
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:45,380
of me...

603
00:38:46,030 --> 00:38:47,030
Uh...

604
00:38:47,090 --> 00:38:48,410
Me? Changing schools?

605
00:38:49,570 --> 00:38:50,686
I'm just traveling to Japan.

606
00:38:50,710 --> 00:38:51,710
Huh?!

607
00:38:51,820 --> 00:38:52,820
Go to Japan?

608
00:38:52,860 --> 00:38:54,846
Does that mean
we'll still be together in Grade 12?

609
00:38:54,870 --> 00:38:56,300
Will we be in the same class?

610
00:38:56,340 --> 00:38:58,140
Who would want to be with
a monster like you?

611
00:39:01,760 --> 00:39:02,760
Tee,

612
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:05,900
just leave me alone already.

613
00:39:05,930 --> 00:39:07,390
Okay, I'm fine with anything

614
00:39:07,420 --> 00:39:08,440
as long as you stay.

615
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:16,170
Is he your friend, Jeab?

616
00:39:16,370 --> 00:39:17,370
Oh, no.

617
00:39:18,920 --> 00:39:19,920
Is he your boyfriend?

618
00:39:20,370 --> 00:39:21,510
What even is that question?

619
00:39:23,500 --> 00:39:24,500
No.

620
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:26,320
He's not your boyfriend.

621
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:27,520
So you're not taken, yeah?

622
00:39:38,900 --> 00:39:40,590
Part-time workers here

623
00:39:40,620 --> 00:39:43,280
receive full welfare benefits,
just like full-time employees.

624
00:39:43,310 --> 00:39:45,750
You don't have to worry

625
00:39:45,820 --> 00:39:48,380
because I'm very kind.

626
00:39:48,430 --> 00:39:50,370
And the owner of this hotel, Mr. Fu,

627
00:39:50,400 --> 00:39:53,220
is very sweet and handsome, too.

628
00:39:59,020 --> 00:40:02,010
This hotel has a lot of handsome men.

629
00:40:02,040 --> 00:40:03,760
Oh, God!

630
00:40:03,800 --> 00:40:04,920
How will I

631
00:40:04,950 --> 00:40:06,980
be able to focus on work?

632
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:10,440
Thank you, Jang.

633
00:40:10,550 --> 00:40:12,280
I will do my best here.

634
00:40:12,420 --> 00:40:14,880
Oh, and don't let work
affect your studies, okay?

635
00:40:14,910 --> 00:40:15,910
Yes.

636
00:40:18,250 --> 00:40:19,480
Oh, wow...

637
00:40:31,980 --> 00:40:33,030
Hey!

638
00:40:39,300 --> 00:40:40,300
What are you doing?

639
00:40:41,110 --> 00:40:42,920
You're just so cute.

640
00:40:43,250 --> 00:40:46,000
Don't you feel like...

641
00:40:47,900 --> 00:40:48,900
No.

642
00:40:52,490 --> 00:40:53,490
Then,

643
00:40:53,830 --> 00:40:55,350
if I want to wake you up,

644
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:56,610
what should I do?

645
00:40:57,490 --> 00:40:58,970
Kissing your neck?

646
00:40:59,580 --> 00:41:00,580
Kissing your lips?

647
00:41:02,110 --> 00:41:04,030
Or...

648
00:41:04,930 --> 00:41:05,930
Hey.

649
00:41:06,690 --> 00:41:08,150
If you want to do that,

650
00:41:08,310 --> 00:41:10,200
I can set the alarm myself.

651
00:41:10,840 --> 00:41:11,840
Doing this

652
00:41:12,900 --> 00:41:13,900
won't help.

653
00:41:15,400 --> 00:41:16,810
Then...

654
00:41:20,990 --> 00:41:21,990
Why?

655
00:41:23,070 --> 00:41:24,790
I can use my hands.

656
00:41:25,170 --> 00:41:26,170
Tian,

657
00:41:27,270 --> 00:41:28,950
we're not even that close.

658
00:41:30,890 --> 00:41:31,890
I can't do this.

659
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:36,280
Mark!

660
00:41:36,540 --> 00:41:37,590
Mark!

661
00:41:39,600 --> 00:41:41,420
You're such a challenge for me.

662
00:42:33,200 --> 00:42:34,480
I'm happy

663
00:42:34,520 --> 00:42:37,680
to be a part of this family.

664
00:42:37,890 --> 00:42:39,390
When you said that...

665
00:42:40,190 --> 00:42:41,500
my heart truly swelled.

666
00:42:46,770 --> 00:42:47,920
Do you remember

667
00:42:48,820 --> 00:42:50,380
what you told me?

668
00:42:51,479 --> 00:42:54,554
"With love, all is as joyous as ever."

669
00:42:55,596 --> 00:42:58,213
"Without love, even perfection turns bitter."

670
00:42:58,900 --> 00:43:00,790
Did you learn how to speak Chinese as well?

671
00:43:01,550 --> 00:43:02,610
I'm so happy.

672
00:43:07,850 --> 00:43:09,890
If you have a close bond with someone,

673
00:43:10,360 --> 00:43:11,600
even when things are difficult,

674
00:43:12,400 --> 00:43:13,600
you can still feel whole.

675
00:43:15,070 --> 00:43:16,420
But without love,

676
00:43:17,270 --> 00:43:18,510
even if you have everything,

677
00:43:18,930 --> 00:43:20,290
your heart will feel empty.

678
00:43:22,300 --> 00:43:24,170
You translated it better than I did.

679
00:43:24,560 --> 00:43:26,020
I used ChatGPT, Fu.

680
00:43:40,630 --> 00:43:41,920
- Go on!
- Kiss!

681
00:43:42,020 --> 00:43:43,200
- Kiss!
- Kiss!

682
00:43:43,260 --> 00:43:44,320
- Kiss!
- Kiss!

683
00:43:44,360 --> 00:43:45,360
- Kiss!
- Kiss!

684
00:43:45,430 --> 00:43:46,300
- Kiss!
- Kiss!
- Kiss!
- Kiss!

685
00:43:47,260 --> 00:43:48,170
Kiss!
Kiss!

686
00:43:49,120 --> 00:43:50,000
Kiss!
Kiss!

687
00:43:50,980 --> 00:43:51,980
Kiss!

688
00:43:52,050 --> 00:43:53,050
Kiss!

689
00:43:53,100 --> 00:43:54,100
Kiss!

690
00:43:54,160 --> 00:43:55,160
Kiss!

691
00:43:55,200 --> 00:43:56,160
Kiss!

692
00:43:56,190 --> 00:43:57,190
Kiss...

693
00:43:58,120 --> 00:43:59,390
Kiss him!

694
00:44:07,450 --> 00:44:08,930
- Aw!
- Wow!

695
00:44:08,960 --> 00:44:10,510
Tee Lek, no peeking.

696
00:45:13,490 --> 00:45:15,010
Little Chicken.

697
00:45:16,960 --> 00:45:17,960
Tee,

698
00:45:18,090 --> 00:45:19,570
didn't you say you'd stop teasing me?

699
00:45:20,110 --> 00:45:22,240
It's not just that
I like to tease you, Jeab.

700
00:45:23,360 --> 00:45:24,630
I like to tease... oops!

701
00:45:25,610 --> 00:45:26,890
I like your rosy cheeks... oops!

702
00:45:27,090 --> 00:45:28,400
I like you... oops!

703
00:45:28,490 --> 00:45:29,720
- That's right!
- That's right!

704
00:45:30,920 --> 00:45:32,280
Woo!

705
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:34,490
I like to tease you

706
00:45:34,980 --> 00:45:36,480
because teasing you...

707
00:45:37,480 --> 00:45:39,590
it means...

708
00:45:40,470 --> 00:45:41,720
Tee, you monster!

709
00:45:46,120 --> 00:45:47,300
Get ready,

710
00:45:47,650 --> 00:45:48,490
Little Chicken.

711
00:45:48,590 --> 00:45:53,190
I'll use a hundred more tricks
to win, win your heart.

712
00:45:56,090 --> 00:46:01,370
(To be continued...)

713
00:46:01,500 --> 00:46:02,720
Get ready.

714
00:46:02,930 --> 00:46:04,570
I'll win your heart in

715
00:46:04,670 --> 00:46:05,670
three...

716
00:46:05,860 --> 00:46:06,860
two...

717
00:46:07,080 --> 00:46:08,080
one...

718
00:46:08,210 --> 00:46:10,510
Hi, guys. I'm Boss, Chaikamon Sermsongwittaya.

719
00:46:10,540 --> 00:46:11,540
I play Fu.

720
00:46:11,570 --> 00:46:13,510
Hello, guys. I'm Noeul, Nuttarat.

721
00:46:13,540 --> 00:46:14,640
I play Moo.

722
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:15,700
I'm Turbo,

723
00:46:15,740 --> 00:46:17,420
Chanokchon Boonmanawong.

724
00:46:17,450 --> 00:46:18,520
I play Tai.

725
00:46:18,550 --> 00:46:20,000
Hello. I'm Donut, Suppawit,

726
00:46:20,030 --> 00:46:21,350
and I play Tian.

727
00:46:21,380 --> 00:46:23,050
My name is Noh, Phouluang Thongprasert.

728
00:46:23,080 --> 00:46:24,280
I play Yu.

729
00:46:24,420 --> 00:46:26,810
My name is Poom, Wachirapanya Milintachinda.

730
00:46:26,840 --> 00:46:28,120
I play Tee.

731
00:46:28,250 --> 00:46:29,200
I'm Effect, guys.

732
00:46:29,230 --> 00:46:30,920
My full name is Narawit Kueanphet,

733
00:46:30,960 --> 00:46:32,380
and I play Jeab.

734
00:46:32,420 --> 00:46:33,916
I'd worked on a drama series.
(How it felt before working on this series)

735
00:46:33,940 --> 00:46:35,820
I'd played all sorts of serious roles,

736
00:46:35,860 --> 00:46:38,710
but I'd never been in a full-on comedy series,

737
00:46:38,750 --> 00:46:41,260
and I wanted to be in one.

738
00:46:41,300 --> 00:46:43,010
This is my third acting project.

739
00:46:43,030 --> 00:46:45,070
What I was really happy about was that

740
00:46:45,100 --> 00:46:46,840
I'd been wanting to take on a role in

741
00:46:46,880 --> 00:46:49,940
a comedy series or comedy film for a long time,

742
00:46:49,980 --> 00:46:52,306
and I was really happy that
I finally got to play this role.

743
00:46:52,330 --> 00:46:55,020
I was fairly excited,
as this is a fairly long series.

744
00:46:55,080 --> 00:46:56,850
This one's based on three novels,

745
00:46:56,880 --> 00:46:59,080
which is very new to me,

746
00:46:59,120 --> 00:47:00,126
as they are all in the same universe.

747
00:47:00,150 --> 00:47:01,790
I immediately accepted the role.

748
00:47:01,830 --> 00:47:03,690
Back at the casting, I said,

749
00:47:03,720 --> 00:47:05,840
"I want to work on this.
I have to be in this one."

750
00:47:05,870 --> 00:47:07,280
I've never been in a series

751
00:47:07,320 --> 00:47:09,520
where the protagonist is this delusional.

752
00:47:09,550 --> 00:47:10,490
I think everyone is going to like it.

753
00:47:10,520 --> 00:47:12,350
After reading the plot, I was like,

754
00:47:12,390 --> 00:47:14,450
"Wow, the story has a lot of variety."

755
00:47:14,500 --> 00:47:17,450
I was quite nervous, as I wanted to do my best.

756
00:47:17,500 --> 00:47:19,150
I felt excited,

757
00:47:19,180 --> 00:47:22,220
since this would be my first series.

758
00:47:22,280 --> 00:47:24,220
I was really happy because

759
00:47:24,280 --> 00:47:25,450
I've been trying very hard

760
00:47:25,480 --> 00:47:28,380
to get into a series since I was in school.

761
00:47:28,420 --> 00:47:30,970
I'm happy that I finally got the role.

762
00:47:31,040 --> 00:47:33,670
I got to express
a completely different version of myself.

763
00:47:33,710 --> 00:47:36,080
Acting in a comedy

764
00:47:36,110 --> 00:47:37,820
requires instinct and trust

765
00:47:37,850 --> 00:47:40,690
when it comes to everything in the play.

766
00:47:40,720 --> 00:47:42,910
It feels like

767
00:47:43,220 --> 00:47:45,100
I get to know myself better

768
00:47:45,130 --> 00:47:48,160
through a different side of myself.

769
00:47:56,120 --> 00:47:58,230
We were stuck at a red light.
(Favorite scene?)

770
00:47:58,260 --> 00:48:00,240
I rolled down the window

771
00:48:00,290 --> 00:48:01,860
and saw Moo on a motorcycle taxi.

772
00:48:01,890 --> 00:48:04,130
That scene, to me, was like

773
00:48:04,180 --> 00:48:06,220
destiny.

774
00:48:06,320 --> 00:48:09,230
In the script, it said something like,

775
00:48:09,260 --> 00:48:11,470
"There are around
500 intersections in Bangkok,

776
00:48:11,610 --> 00:48:13,116
yet you have to be stuck in
the same red light as me,

777
00:48:13,140 --> 00:48:14,210
leading us to meet."

778
00:48:14,240 --> 00:48:16,890
I think it was such an amazing start

779
00:48:16,930 --> 00:48:17,930
for this series.

780
00:48:17,960 --> 00:48:19,200
It's the scenes with Fu

781
00:48:19,230 --> 00:48:20,480
where it's

782
00:48:20,530 --> 00:48:22,610
romantic, but with comedy mixed in.

783
00:48:22,650 --> 00:48:24,670
I feel like everything in those scenes

784
00:48:24,710 --> 00:48:28,470
had a lot of attention to detail
in terms of the characters.

785
00:48:28,510 --> 00:48:30,410
As for my unforgettable moment,

786
00:48:30,440 --> 00:48:32,730
it would be the tea-brewing scene.

787
00:48:32,760 --> 00:48:34,576
It was difficult.
I kept twirling the kettle around.

788
00:48:34,600 --> 00:48:36,080
I almost hit myself with it.

789
00:48:36,120 --> 00:48:40,290
I was impressed with the scene with Fu and Tee,

790
00:48:40,510 --> 00:48:43,670
where we were eating popcorn together

791
00:48:44,120 --> 00:48:46,320
and talking about Lhee,

792
00:48:46,350 --> 00:48:47,820
Moo's sister.

793
00:48:47,870 --> 00:48:49,970
That scene was especially fun.

794
00:48:50,000 --> 00:48:51,000
I felt like

795
00:48:51,030 --> 00:48:54,090
everyone just clicked,

796
00:48:54,430 --> 00:48:55,500
and it was both funny

797
00:48:55,530 --> 00:48:57,260
and scary at the same time.

798
00:48:57,290 --> 00:48:58,460
It's the ending scene.

799
00:48:58,500 --> 00:49:00,880
You guys get to see how characters develop.

800
00:49:00,920 --> 00:49:02,210
It was something that...

801
00:49:02,240 --> 00:49:04,030
It was the kind of ending

802
00:49:04,060 --> 00:49:05,220
that made me smile.

803
00:49:05,250 --> 00:49:06,540
And I believe

804
00:49:06,580 --> 00:49:08,330
you will feel the same after watching it.

805
00:49:08,360 --> 00:49:10,770
It was the scene where I shielded Tai
from the water splash.

806
00:49:10,800 --> 00:49:11,580
It felt like...

807
00:49:11,620 --> 00:49:14,510
I've never shot a slow-motion scene,

808
00:49:15,030 --> 00:49:17,990
where I get soaked and stuff.

809
00:49:18,310 --> 00:49:20,760
But I think I managed to pull it off.

810
00:49:20,790 --> 00:49:23,150
It'd be the scene where I was chasing Jeab,

811
00:49:23,260 --> 00:49:25,770
thinking that he was dropping out of the school.

812
00:49:26,080 --> 00:49:29,860
After working with Jeab for so long,
I managed to squeeze my tears out for him.

813
00:49:29,890 --> 00:49:32,720
I never thought I'd be able to do that.

814
00:49:32,760 --> 00:49:36,036
My favorite has to be the scene where
Tee gets into a fight to get my notebook back.

815
00:49:36,060 --> 00:49:36,880
I was really impressed

816
00:49:36,920 --> 00:49:39,210
because someone chose to fight for me

817
00:49:39,250 --> 00:49:41,330
just to get my belongings back.

818
00:49:41,370 --> 00:49:42,210
I was happy that.

819
00:49:42,250 --> 00:49:45,270
Poom went out of his way
to fight for me like that.

820
00:49:53,330 --> 00:49:55,990
(Three words for your character)

821
00:49:56,190 --> 00:49:56,900
"Warm,

822
00:49:56,990 --> 00:49:57,990
reliable,

823
00:49:58,300 --> 00:49:59,410
and likable," I'd say.

824
00:49:59,550 --> 00:50:00,210
"Sweet,

825
00:50:00,450 --> 00:50:01,450
lively,

826
00:50:01,500 --> 00:50:02,230
and a bottom."

827
00:50:02,400 --> 00:50:03,430
"Acting real tough."

828
00:50:03,470 --> 00:50:06,000
Tai is the most reserved character, you see.

829
00:50:06,090 --> 00:50:06,910
"So insanely fantastic."

830
00:50:06,950 --> 00:50:08,020
You've seen my character

831
00:50:08,060 --> 00:50:10,150
from his looks to his mannerisms

832
00:50:10,180 --> 00:50:11,240
and character development.

833
00:50:11,270 --> 00:50:13,330
With all three together, it's fantastic.

834
00:50:13,360 --> 00:50:15,640
Since Yu is diligent,

835
00:50:15,910 --> 00:50:17,196
my three words for him would be...

836
00:50:17,220 --> 00:50:19,030
"Never feel tired?"

837
00:50:19,390 --> 00:50:20,280
"Stubborn,
a teaser,

838
00:50:21,080 --> 00:50:23,370
and playful."

839
00:50:23,520 --> 00:50:24,440
"It's so Jeab."

840
00:50:24,500 --> 00:50:26,800
I believe Tai has more sides to him

841
00:50:26,890 --> 00:50:29,060
as a character

842
00:50:29,100 --> 00:50:31,380
beyond when he's with his friends

843
00:50:31,500 --> 00:50:33,070
and siblings.

844
00:50:33,100 --> 00:50:35,060
There must also be a side of him when he's alone.

845
00:50:35,090 --> 00:50:37,990
It still needs to be explored further

846
00:50:38,030 --> 00:50:39,030
in future installments.

847
00:50:39,060 --> 00:50:41,810
If Tian were a real person?

848
00:50:41,840 --> 00:50:44,380
I think he'd be someone

